===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|庚|同|c1=s|c2=p|abb1=y|ls=psc|ls2=ic|tr2=*lˤoŋ}}.

Probably the original graph of {{zh-l|鏞}} (“large bell”), formed from {{zh-l|庚}} plus {{zh-l|同}} / {{zh-l|用}}.

===Etymology===
Originally “large bell; hollow resonant vessel”. In bronze inscriptions, 庸 is also used for “capacity; volume”, consistent with an earlier sense referring to a hollow object. “To use; to employ” is probably a later development influenced by {{zh-l|用}}, and “ordinary; common” is later still.

